<TEXT>
president bush an avid baseball fan took his 
13yearold grandson and the budget director to an american league 
baseball game wednesday at baltimores memorial stadium 
the president and grandson george p bush stayed through six 
innings of an evening game between the firstplace baltimore orioles 
and thirdplace toronto blue jays with them were budget director 
richard darman and his son willie also 13 
the presidential party left with the score tied 11 in the top of 
the seventh the orioles won it 21 
bush and his party sat in a sky box over home plate with orioles 
owner eli jacobs bush took off his suitcoat and tie and waved to 
the crowd at the beginning of the game 
the president who keeps his firstbasemans glove in his oval 
office desk was captain of yales baseball team in 1948 his senior 
year 
bush threw out the first ball when he and egyptian president 
hosni mubarak attended the april 3 season opener between the orioles 
and the boston red sox this trip the white house said bush was 
expected to merely watch the game from a sky box 
young george the son of jeb and columba bush has been staying 
at the white house for several weeks 
 
</TEXT>
