falling oil prices demanded by lenders mexico is now seeking a 55 
percent reduction in the nearly 70 billion it owes private 
creditors 
the commercial banks countered that plea with an offer of a 15 
percent reduction talks between the two parties are continuing 
but without a general agreement by july 14 when the paris 
economic summit of major industrialized nations opens 
administration officials fear bradys debt reduction plan like 
that of his predecessor james a baker iii may come unraveled 
debtridden poor countries claim a 20 percent reduction is not 
enough to allow them to lift up their economies 
and other lender nations are skeptical at the plans ultimate 
reliance upon taxpayer assistance through the world bank and 
international monetary fund to guarantee private banks against 
further losses 
time is running short and uncertainties appear to be 
increasing said taylor 
