spending to go directly to lowincome parents to help them pay for 
child care including the use of vouchers or other certificates 
created by state governments twentytwo percent of the money in the 
senate plan would be for loans grants and training programs 
designed to expand childcare opportunity and quality with the 
remaining 8 percent used for state administrative costs 
