<TEXT>
the case of a us soldier 
sentenced to 30 years in prison for giving military secrets to east 
germany will be reviewed by a general who may reduce the sentence 
an army spokesman said wednesday 
michael a peri of laguna niguel calif pleaded guilty to 
espionage last week during his courtmartial in fulda where he was 
based with the 11th armored cavalry regiment near the east german 
border 
before he was sentenced saturday the 22yearold intelligence 
analyst tearfully begged forgiveness for leaving his unit in 
february and turning over defense plans to the east germans he 
denied receiving any money for the plans 
under a pretrial agreement peris 30year sentence will be 
reduced to 25 years if he serves the first three with good behavior 
peri also received a dishonorable discharge lost his pay and 
benefits and was demoted from specialist four to the armys lowest 
rank private 1 
the case must be reviewed by lt gen john w woodmansee the 
commander of the us armys 5th corps in frankfurt said corps 
spokesman maj samuel taylor 
gen woodmansee as the convening authority for the case 
automatically reviews it and if he finds grounds to do so can 
choose to reduce the sentence taylor said 
the case then is sent to the us court of military review in 
falls church va for review 
even if woodmansee chooses to reduce the sentence the review 
court can further reduce it they can never increase it so all of 
this is in peris favor taylor said 
peri can ask that the case be reviewed again by a panel of three 
civilian judges at the court of military appeals in washington and 
as a last resort he can petition the us supreme court 
peri left the 11th regiment on feb 20 and went to east germany 
with a portable army computer and discs containing classified 
material 
he returned voluntarily march 4 the regiment is responsible for 
frontline defense if soviet bloc forces attack 
peri said he left because he was frustrated with his job as an 
intelligence analyst and electronic signal intercepter 
military officials described him as a model soldier before his 
disappearance 
peri is being held at an army jail in mannheim pending transfer 
to the militarys disciplinary barracks at fort leavenworth kan 
