a clotbusting drug that interrupts heart attacks 
has been redesigned to work longer which might reduce the risk of a 
second heart attack after treatment 
in test tube experiments an altered version of a drug called 
tissue plasminogen activator remained largely potent when exposed to 
substances in blood that deactivate the current form of the drug 
the work is described in thursdays issue of the british journal 
