in lebanon while aoun is armed by iraq damascus chief arab foe 
following the contacts and a consolidated ceasefire the 
committee said it will invite lebanons singlechamber parliament to 
a foreign country of legislators choice to work out a new 
powersharing formula christian sects traditionally have dominated 
lebanese politics though they are outnumbered 21 by sunni and 
shiite moslems and the minority druse 
the ceasefire lifting of blockades and opening of crossing 
links must be achieved before the meeting of the parliamentarians 
outside lebanon which will set the stage for the meeting of the 
lebanese parliament in lebanon the committee said 
christian legislators welcomed the calls for a ceasefire and 
