the measure was passed tuesday by the state assembly and senate 
and sent to gov bob miller and aides said the governor will sign 
it 
nevada has the fifthhighest car insurance rates in the nation 
with an average premium of 600 per driver according to the state 
insurance commissioner 
the measure would let insurers raise rates only if they could 
prove to the insurance commissioner that they would go bankrupt 
without the increase 
that is the toughest in my opinion rate rollback bill in 
america said assemblyman gene porter who negotiated the rollback 
with the senate 
the assembly approved the measure 375 and the state senate then 
voted 164 for it 
auto insurers termed unconstitutional a provision taking into 
account profits from fire health and life insurance when deciding 
whether an insurer could raise rates on auto liability coverage 
the language in this bill is more patently unconstitutional 
than the language in prop 103 american insurance assocation 
spokesman jim wadhams said referring to a california rate rollback 
parts of proposition 103 were struck down by that states supreme 
court on grounds they denied insurers a fair return on their 
investments 
wadhams also complained that lawmakers hadnt let insurers 
participate in compromise negotiations 
the insurance commissioners office estimates auto insurance 
prices have risen 5 percent in the last year making the bills 
average rollback more than 20 percent 
