premier 
abalkin was among four cabinet members confirmed wednesday after 
the legislature rejected for the first time in soviet history a 
slate of nominees for the government positions 
the situation in the country is that of an emergency abalkin 
said within the last year and a half the economic situation has 
been worsening with every passing month 
the economist said 12 million to 15 million people will become 
unemployed as a result of reform by the end of the century 
according to remarks carried by the tass news agency 
abalkin said the layoffs will occur as the country moves from 
emphasis on production to services and as the labor force is 
redistributed from state businesses to private cooperatives and 
familyrun businesses 
other economists have said unemployment will result from 
streamlining the government and industry and shifting resources 
within the economy 
abalkin the 59yearold director of the institute of economics 
told the legislators the unemployed will need job retraining 
occupational counseling and other social programs 
traditional communist party doctrine has said unemployment is 
solely a western problem resulting from exploitation of the working 
class but president mikhail s gorbachevs program of perestroika 
or economic restructuring is causing widespread realignment of the 
soviet labor force 
